cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a deep neural network model to address the issue of out-of-vocabulary words. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with building intelligent dialogue systems. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes a neural network model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper investigates the impact of end-of-utterance and end-of-turn token tags on performance.
